Sonic Pulse	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:GulgarRaceTrait.SpecialAttack.Extraordinary.Breath Weapon	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:As a standard action, a gulgar can emit a 30-foot cone of sound that deals 3d6 points of sonic damage and may deafen foes. Any creature in the area must succeed on a DC %1 Fortitude save or be deafened for 1 hour. Deafened creatures cannot be further deafened, but they still take the sonic damage from other sonic pulse attacks. Once it has used this ability, a gulgar must wait 1d4 rounds before using it again. This is a sonic effect. The save DC is Constitution-based.|BreathWeaponCone|BreathWeaponDice|BreathWeaponDamageDie|BreathWeaponDC	KEY:Gulgar ~ Sonic Pulse				DEFINE:BreathWeaponCone|0	DEFINE:BreathWeaponDice|0	DEFINE:BreathWeaponDamageDie|0	DEFINE:BreathWeaponDC|0		BONUS:VAR|BreathWeaponCone|30	BONUS:VAR|BreathWeaponDice|3	BONUS:VAR|BreathWeaponDamageDie|6|TYPE=Base	BONUS:VAR|BreathWeaponDC|DefaultDCCon	BONUS:VAR|BreathWeaponDC|2|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Ability Focus (Breath Weapon)					ABILITY:Ability Focus|AUTOMATIC|Breath Weapon									SOURCEPAGE:MM3	
